The Ox is obviously short of confidence atm, not helped by being benched after a couple of poor games when more expensive players have been given 10+ games of playing bad in the past, but I feel he can be Arsenal and England's long-term solution on the right. Other than him, I don't expect the first XI to change from the one that beat Bayern, maybe Giroud up front instead of Walcott. It's a 50-50 decision this season. We're playing well atm and I expect a win whoever is up front. 2-0, Sanchez MotM.
